{"_id":"0cp0lcUIm3NEZfMN","name":"Battle Anthem","type":"feat","img":"UESTRPG/Icons/Alliance/Assault/ON-icon-skill-Assault-War_Horn.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<h2><span id=\"Battle_Anthem\" class=\"mw-headline\">Battle Anthem</span></h2>\n<p>At 14th level, you gain the ability to use your instruments or voice to inspire your allies in the heat of battle. As an action, all allies or enemies within 60 feet of you that can see and hear you, gain one effect of your choice for the duration of the anthem. The effect lasts up to 1 minute, as though you are concentrating on a spell. As an action on your following turns you can change the effect of your Battle Anthem.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Anthem of War.</strong></em> Each ally that can see and hear you gains advantage on attack rolls for the duration.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Anthem of Protection.</strong></em> Each ally that can see and hear you gains a +2 bonus to their AC for the duration.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Anthem of Intimidation.</strong></em> Each enemy that can see and hear you has disadvantage on saving throws for the duration.</p>\n<p>Once you use this feature, you must finish a long rest to be able to use it again.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Basic Rules v1.4 pg 39","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"any","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":60,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"lr"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"College of Solitude 14","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[{"_id":"fgBcD69ZE46p8V0q","changes":[{"key":"flags.midi-qol.disadvantage.ability.save.all","mode":5,"value":"1","priority":"20"}],"disabled":true,"duration":{"startTime":null,"rounds":10},"icon":"UESTRPG/Icons/Alliance/Assault/ON-icon-skill-Assault-Aggressive_Horn.png","label":"Anthem of Intimidation","origin":"Item.0cp0lcUIm3NEZfMN","transfer":false,"flags":{"core":{"statusId":""},"dae":{"stackable":"none","macroRepeat":"none","specialDuration":[],"transfer":false}},"tint":null,"selectedKey":"flags.midi-qol.disadvantage.ability.save.all"},{"_id":"AZLDvCzGrPEQ52G4","changes":[{"key":"data.attributes.ac.bonus","mode":2,"value":"2","priority":"20"}],"disabled":true,"duration":{"startTime":null,"rounds":10},"icon":"UESTRPG/Icons/Alliance/Assault/ON-icon-skill-Assault-Sturdy_Horn.png","label":"Anthem of Protection","origin":"Item.0cp0lcUIm3NEZfMN","transfer":false,"flags":{"core":{"statusId":""},"dae":{"stackable":"none","macroRepeat":"none","specialDuration":[],"transfer":false}},"tint":null,"selectedKey":"data.attributes.ac.bonus"},{"_id":"fGTmmAQpJYrjdvtw","changes":[{"key":"flags.midi-qol.advantage.attack.all","mode":5,"value":"1","priority":"20"}],"disabled":true,"duration":{"startTime":null,"rounds":10},"icon":"UESTRPG/Icons/Alliance/Assault/ON-icon-skill-Assault-War_Horn.png","label":"Anthem of War","origin":"Item.0cp0lcUIm3NEZfMN","transfer":false,"flags":{"core":{"statusId":""},"dae":{"stackable":"none","macroRepeat":"none","specialDuration":[],"transfer":false}},"tint":null,"selectedKey":"flags.midi-qol.advantage.attack.all"}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_c9gn4tl1e8m","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Bard Feats#/CF_SEP/Solitude","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"1YsPYbXZRy2GPdBB","name":"Danger Sense","type":"feat","img":"modules/uestrpg5e/artwork/ESO/ability/Classes/passive/dragonknight_020.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<h2><span id=\"Danger_Sense\" class=\"mw-headline\">Danger Sense</span></h2>\n<p>At 2nd level, you gain an uncanny sense of when things nearby aren’t as they should be, giving you an edge when you dodge away from danger. You have advantage on Agility saving throws against effects that you can see, such as traps and spells. To gain this benefit, you can’t be blinded, deafened, or incapacitated.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Basic Rules v1.4 pg 29","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":"","long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"type":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"requirements":"Barbarian 2","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[{"_id":"1B322SOXM74Jxmvt","changes":[{"key":"flags.midi-qol.advantage.ability.save.dex","mode":5,"value":"1","priority":"10"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"modules/uestrpg5e/artwork/ESO/ability/Classes/passive/dragonknight_020.png","label":"Danger Sense","origin":"Item.1YsPYbXZRy2GPdBB","transfer":true,"flags":{"core":{"statusId":""},"dae":{"stackable":"none","macroRepeat":"none","specialDuration":[],"transfer":true,"durationExpression":""}},"tint":null,"selectedKey":"flags.midi-qol.advantage.ability.save.dex"}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_xgt9dlxpc7","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Barbarian Feats","color":"#000000","sort":-12500}}}
{"_id":"1fLSVpAKYDl6fHhG","name":"Reaver's Verdict","type":"feat","img":"modules/uestrpg5e/artwork/ESO/ability/buff/minor_brutality.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<h2><span id=\"Reaper.27s_Verdict\" class=\"mw-headline\">Reaper's Verdict</span></h2>\n<p>Beginning at 14th level, while raging, you can attack three times, instead of twice, whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Basic Rules v1.4 pg 31","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Path of the Reaver 14","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_vfyg1ixv6gq","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Barbarian Feats#/CF_SEP/Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"1iSc6bbBqbAt9D23","name":"Alteration Prodigy","type":"feat","img":"UESTRPG/Icons/Magic/SR-skill-Alteration.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<h2><span id=\"Alteration_Prodigy\" class=\"mw-headline\">Alteration Prodigy</span></h2>\n<p>Beginning when you select this school at 2nd level, the gold and time you must spend to learn an alteration spell is halved.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 117","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"School of Alteration 2","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_21023tz1rns","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Mage Feats#/CF_SEP/Alteration","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"2NbYKSZdKDznoTXp","name":"Fighting Style: Great Weapon Fighting","type":"feat","img":"modules/uestrpg5e/artwork/ESO/ability/Weapons/weapon/027.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><strong>Great Weapon Fighting.</strong></em> When you roll a 1 or 2 on a damage die for an attack you make with a melee weapon that you are wielding with two hands, you can reroll the die and must use the new roll. The weapon must have the two-handed or versatile property for you to gain this benefit.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>GM Note: Add `r&lt;2` to the attack roll formula for great weapons this character owns.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"BR v1.4 pg. 42","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":"","long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"type":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"requirements":"Crusader 2","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dnd5e.classfeatures.3Nc6u9pyStByuJsm"},"cf":{"id":"temp_u2xacoez7re","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Crusader Feats","color":"#000000","sort":600000}}}
{"_id":"2OGNPqZ66bs8gZVg","name":"Heavylifting","type":"feat","img":"modules/uestrpg5e/artwork/ESO/ability/Weapons/dualwield/006.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<h2><span id=\"Heavylifting\" class=\"mw-headline\">Heavylifting</span></h2>\n<p>Beginning at 10th level, while raging and not wearing heavy armor, you are able to engage in two-weapon fighting with all weapons except for those with the heavy or two handed traits. <br /><br />Additionally, weapons with the heavy or two handed traits can be held in one hand.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Basic Rules v1.4 pg 32","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Path of the Savage 10","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qnqylys0v9","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Barbarian Feats#/CF_SEP/Savage","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"2RuuS883eOfYRJFl","name":"Brutal Critical","type":"feat","img":"modules/uestrpg5e/artwork/ESO/ability/Classes/passive/dragonknight_014.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<h2><span id=\"Brutal_Critical\" class=\"mw-headline\">Brutal Critical</span></h2>\n<p>Starting at 9th level, you can roll one additional weapon damage die when determining the extra damage for a critical hit with a melee attack. This increases to two additional dice at 13th level, and three additional dice at 17th level.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Basic Rules v1.4 pg 30","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":"","long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"type":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"requirements":"Barbarian 9","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[{"_id":"IRp0LNLt1vp4qSVz","flags":{"dae":{"stackable":"none","transfer":true,"durationExpression":"","macroRepeat":"none","specialDuration":[]},"core":{"statusId":""}},"changes":[{"key":"flags.dnd5e.meleeCriticalDamageDice","mode":2,"value":"floor((@classes.barbarian.levels - 5) / 4)","priority":"20"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"modules/uestrpg5e/artwork/ESO/ability/Classes/passive/dragonknight_014.png","label":"Brutal Critical","tint":null,"transfer":true,"selectedKey":"flags.dnd5e.meleeCriticalDamageDice"}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"dae":{"activeEquipped":false,"alwaysActive":true},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.616Bz1dtN9LhGrGS"},"cf":{"id":"temp_xgt9dlxpc7"}}}
{"_id":"2jwdtr84QEHhpuSN","name":"Life Amid Death","type":"feat","img":"modules/uestrpg5e/artwork/ESO/ability/Classes/necromancer/016.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<h2><span id=\"Life_Amid_Death\" class=\"mw-headline\">Life Amid Death</span></h2>\n<p>At 6th level, you can cause a burst of restorative energy when a creature dies. When you use your Soul Harvest feature, you can use a reaction to instantly restore hit points to each ally within 10 feet of the corpse. The amount of hit points restored is equal to the creatures CR rating (minimum of 1).</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"EoE pg. 16","activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"ally"},"range":{"value":10,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Flesh Sculptor 6","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_y2v6h8s8if","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Necromancer Feats#/CF_SEP/Flesh Sculpter","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"2tmyLIj8FHgKfvWx","name":"Necromantic Art","type":"feat","img":"modules/uestrpg5e/artwork/ESO/ability/Classes/necromancer/003.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<h3><span id=\"Necromantic_Art\" class=\"mw-headline\">Necromantic Art</span></h3>\n<p>When you reach 2nd level, your continued pursuit of the dark arts begins to express itself in a necromantic art of your choice. Your choice grants you features at 2nd, 6th, 14th, and 18th level.</p>\n<table class=\"uestrpgtable mw-collapsible mw-made-collapsible\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th>Art</th>\n<th> </th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"uestrpgtable mw-collapsible mw-made-collapsible\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th>Source</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a title=\"EoE:Baleful Summoner\" href=\"https://wiki.uestrpg.com/wiki/EoE:Baleful_Summoner\">Baleful Summoner</a></td>\n<td>Enemies of Elsweyr</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a title=\"EoE:Deathbringer\" href=\"https://wiki.uestrpg.com/wiki/EoE:Deathbringer\">Deathbringer</a></td>\n<td>Enemies of Elsweyr</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a title=\"EoE:Flesh Sculptor\" href=\"https://wiki.uestrpg.com/wiki/EoE:Flesh_Sculptor\">Flesh Sculptor</a></td>\n<td>Enemies of Elsweyr</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a title=\"EoE:Undying Warrior\" href=\"https://wiki.uestrpg.com/wiki/EoE:Undying_Warrior\">Undying Warrior</a></td>\n<td>Enemies of Elsweyr</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a title=\"LGtC:Corpse Whisperer\" href=\"https://wiki.uestrpg.com/wiki/LGtC:Corpse_Whisperer\">Corpse Whisperer</a></td>\n<td>Legionnaire's Guide to Cyrodiil</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a title=\"LGtC:Sanguine Puppetry\" href=\"https://wiki.uestrpg.com/wiki/LGtC:Sanguine_Puppetry\">Sanguine Puppetry</a></td>\n<td>Legionnaire's Guide to Cyrodiil</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a title=\"LGtC:Voidkeeper\" href=\"https://wiki.uestrpg.com/wiki/LGtC:Voidkeeper\">Voidkeeper</a></td>\n<td>Legionnaire's Guide to Cyrodiil</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3><span id=\"Art_Spells\" class=\"mw-headline\">Art Spells</span></h3>\n<p>Each necromantic art has a list of associated spells. You learn these spells at the levels specified in the necromantic art description. Art spells don't count against the number of spells known. If you gain an art spell that doesn't appear on the <a title=\"EoE:Necromancer Spells\" href=\"https://wiki.uestrpg.com/wiki/EoE:Necromancer_Spells\">necromancer spell list</a>, the spell is nonetheless a necromancer spell for you.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Enemies of Elsweyr pg 10","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Necromancer 2","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_2vjba2j87na","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Necromancer Feats","color":"#000000"}}}
