{"_id":"DkbMS2TKiQ0uctPd","name":"Undead Thralls","type":"feat","img":"modules/uestrpg5e/artwork/ESO/ability/Classes/necromancer/002.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<h2><span id=\"Undead_Thralls\" class=\"mw-headline\">Undead Thralls</span></h2>\n<p>At 6th level, when you cast a spell that animates the dead, you can target one additional corpse or pile of bones, creating another zombie or skeleton, as appropriate. Whenever you create an undead using a necromancy spell, it has additional benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The creature's hit point maximum is increased by an amount equal to your necromancer level.</li>\n<li>The creature adds your proficiency bonus to its weapon damage rolls.</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Enemies of Elsweyr pg 10","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Baleful Summoner 6","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_jc2f383nlwg","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Necromancer Feats#/CF_SEP/Baleful Summoner","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"Dm5YS2C9akgYPaUe","name":"Manipulator of Death","type":"feat","img":"UESTRPG/Icons/Classes/Necromancer/Grave%20Death/ON-icon-skill-Grave_Lord-Venom_Skull.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<h2><span id=\"Manipulator_of_Death\" class=\"mw-headline\">Manipulator of Death</span></h2>\n<p>At 14th level, you can use fragments of soul energy to manipulate your spells and attacks to bring death and decay. When you cast a spell that deals acid, cold, fire, force, or lightning damage, or when you deal damage from a weapon attack, you can expend one Soul Point to replace that damage with your choice of either necrotic or poison damage. You can only replace one type of damage from the attack.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"EoE pg. 15","activation":{"type":"none","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":""},"consume":{"type":"attribute","target":"","amount":1},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Deathbringer 14","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_a1cuhktmv3t","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Necromancer Feats#/CF_SEP/Deathbringer","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"EHQTQEnEabg2KqXr","name":"Cleansing Touch","type":"feat","img":"icons/magic/light/hand-sparks-smoke-teal.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Beginning at 14th level, you can use your action to end one spell on yourself or on one willing creature that you touch.</p><p>You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Charisma modifier (a minimum of once). You regain expended uses when you finish a long rest.</p><p><em>**Foundry note: Note the limited uses is set to the base default of 1 per long rest. Please manually adjust as required.</em></p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 85","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":"Target must be willing."},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"touch"},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"max(1, @abilities.cha.mod)","per":"lr","type":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"requirements":"Paladin 14","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dnd5e.classfeatures.U7BIPVPsptBmwsnV"},"cf":{"id":"temp_u2xacoez7re","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Crusader Feats","color":"#000000","sort":1002052}}}
{"_id":"EL8A53WFhEchUyuV","name":"Shadow Refuge","type":"feat","img":"UESTRPG/Icons/Classes/Nightblade/Assassination/ON-icon-skill-Assassination-Lotus_Fan.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<h2><span id=\"Shadow_Refuge\" class=\"mw-headline\">Shadow Refuge</span></h2>\n<p>At 6th level, you gain the ability to step into a shadow refuge. As an action, you disappear from the world for a brief moment and enter the Shadow Realm, taking advantage of its timeless nature. While in your shadow refuge, you can take two actions to cast spells that target only you. After using those two actions, you return to the space you occupied and your turn ends. Once you use this feature, you can’t use it again until you finish a long rest.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Basic Rules v1.4 pg 74","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":2,"units":"turn"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1","per":"lr"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Seeker 6","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_55zyvlsizdr","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Nightblade Feats#/CF_SEP/Seeker","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"Ef3I7KgjZCYlwUDU","name":"Honorable Combat","type":"feat","img":"icons/skills/melee/weapons-crossed-swords-yellow.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em><strong>Honorable Combat.</strong></em> As a bonus action, you challenge a creature that you can see that is within 30 feet of you to honorable combat. You gain a bonus to your attack rolls equal to your Personality modifier when you attack this creature. This effect ends if a creature other than you attacks your target.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Basic Rules v1.4 pg 45","activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"any","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":30,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":""},"consume":{"type":"attribute","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Knight 3","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[{"_id":"pJ7LPi6Hpjsdkol1","changes":[{"key":"flags.midi-qol.optional.NAME.attack","mode":2,"value":"@abilities.cha.mod","priority":"20"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"rounds":9999,"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/skills/melee/weapons-crossed-swords-yellow.webp","label":"Honorable Combat","origin":"Item.Ef3I7KgjZCYlwUDU","transfer":true,"flags":{"core":{"statusId":""},"dae":{"stackable":"none","macroRepeat":"none","specialDuration":["shortRest","longRest"],"transfer":true}},"tint":null,"selectedKey":"flags.midi-qol.optional.NAME.attack"}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3bhgt0recsj","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Crusader Feats#/CF_SEP/Knight","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"EuIZkXFyRT8Wjban","name":"Divine Sense","type":"feat","img":"modules/uestrpg5e/artwork/ESO/ability/Classes/templar/008.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<h2><span id=\"Divine_Sense\" class=\"mw-headline\">Divine Sense</span></h2>\n<p><em>1st-level crusader feature</em></p>\n<p>The presence of strong evil registers on your senses like a noxious odor, and powerful good rings like heavenly music in your ears. As an action, you can open your awareness to detect such forces. Until the end of your next turn, you know the location of any celestial (aedra), fiend (daedra), or undead within 60 feet of you that is not behind total cover. You know the type of any being whose presence you sense, but not its identity. Within the same radius, you also detect the presence of any place or object that has been consecrated or desecrated, as with the <a class=\"extiw\" title=\"dndbeyond:spells/hallow\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/hallow\"><em>hallow</em></a> spell.</p>\n<p>You can use this feature a number of times equal to 1 + your Personality modifier. When you finish a long rest, you regain all expended uses.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"BR v1.4 pg. 42","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"round"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":60,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":1,"max":"1 + @abilities.cha.mod","per":"lr"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Crusader 1","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[{"_id":"cgGYgPO5aOPPKnik","changes":[{"key":"data.attributes.senses.special","mode":2,"value":"Aedra, Daedra, and Undead within 60ft","priority":"20"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"rounds":2,"startTime":null},"icon":"modules/uestrpg5e/artwork/ESO/ability/Classes/templar/008.png","label":"Divine Sense","origin":"Item.EuIZkXFyRT8Wjban","transfer":false,"flags":{"core":{"statusId":""},"dae":{"stackable":"none","macroRepeat":"none","specialDuration":["turnEnd"],"transfer":false,"durationExpression":""}},"tint":null,"selectedKey":"data.attributes.senses.special"}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u2xacoez7re","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Crusader Feats","color":"#000000","sort":-100000}}}
{"_id":"F9PI19XnXeIbjJr6","name":"Elemental Mastery: Pyromancer","type":"feat","img":"UESTRPG/Icons/Weapon/Destro/ON-icon-skill-Destruction_Staff-Fire_Storm.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<h2><span id=\"Elemental_Mastery\" class=\"mw-headline\">Elemental Mastery</span></h2>\n<p>At level 2, you choose one type of element to have exceptional power over.</p>\n<h3><span id=\"Pyromancer\" class=\"mw-headline\">Pyromancer</span></h3>\n<p>You have a gift for wielding fire, and you use it to burn your enemies to cinders.</p>\n<p>When you cast a spell that deals fire damage, you can reroll the lowest damage die. If the new roll is higher than the original, use it when calculating the damage.</p>\n<p>When you reach 11th level, you can reroll the lowest 2 damage rolls.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 117","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"School of Destruction 2","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_w04ihw3ubv","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Mage Feats#/CF_SEP/Destruction","color":"#000000"}}}
