{"_id":"QmnhzV8xjY2mHqxY","name":"Accelerated Regeneration","type":"feat","img":"modules/uestrpg5e/artwork/ESO/ability/Classes/dragonknight/011_b.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<h2><span id=\"Accelerated_Regeneration\" class=\"mw-headline\">Accelerated Regeneration</span></h2>\n<p>When you choose this path at 3rd level, your wounds naturally stitch together at a faster rate. When you use hit dice to recover hit points during a short rest, you gain additional hit points equal to 1d12 + your Endurance modifier.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Basic Rules v1.4 pg 31","activation":{"type":"special","cost":null,"condition":"When you use hit dice to recover hit points during a short rest"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"con","actionType":"heal","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[["1d12 + @abilities.con.mod","healing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Path of the Reaver 3","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"midi-qol":{"effectActivation":false},"cf":{"id":"temp_vfyg1ixv6gq","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Barbarian Feats#/CF_SEP/Reaver","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"RWAPqoTFYGo5w3UF","name":"Art Spells (Copy)","type":"feat","img":"modules/uestrpg5e/artwork/ESO/ability/Classes/necromancer/003_b.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<h2><span id=\"Art_Spells\" class=\"mw-headline\">Art Spells</span></h2>\n<p>You gain art spells at the necromancer levels listed.</p>\n<table class=\"uestrpgtable\"><caption>Baleful Summoner Art Spells</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th>Level</th>\n<th>Spells</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3rd</td>\n<td><a title=\"EoE:Necromancer Spells\" href=\"https://wiki.uestrpg.com/wiki/EoE:Necromancer_Spells\"><em>grave grasp</em></a>, <a class=\"extiw\" title=\"dndbeyond:spells/warding-bond\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/warding-bond\"><em>warding bond</em> </a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5th</td>\n<td><a class=\"extiw\" title=\"dndbeyond:spells/animate-dead\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/animate-dead\"><em>animate dead</em></a>, <a class=\"extiw\" title=\"dndbeyond:spells/speak-with-dead\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/speak-with-dead\"><em>speak with dead</em></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>7th</td>\n<td><a title=\"EoE:Necromancer Spells\" href=\"https://wiki.uestrpg.com/wiki/EoE:Necromancer_Spells\"><em>animate skeletal mage</em></a>, <a title=\"EoE:Necromancer Spells\" href=\"https://wiki.uestrpg.com/wiki/EoE:Necromancer_Spells\"><em>blast bones</em></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>9th</td>\n<td><a class=\"extiw\" title=\"dndbeyond:spells/danse-macabre\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/danse-macabre\"><em>danse macabre</em></a>, <a class=\"extiw\" title=\"dndbeyond:spells/antilife-shell\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/antilife-shell\"><em>antilife shell</em></a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Enemies of Elsweyr pg 10","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Baleful Summoner","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_h17d0wzw8za","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Necromancer Feats#/CF_SEP/Voidkeeper","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"RvUmEawwhikIJHiK","name":"Improved Minor Illusion","type":"feat","img":"UESTRPG/Icons/Classes/Nightblade/Shadow/ON-icon-skill-Shadow-Dark_Vigor.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<h2><span id=\"Improved_Minor_Illusion\" class=\"mw-headline\">Improved Minor Illusion</span></h2>\n<p>When you choose this school at 2nd level, you learn the <a class=\"extiw\" title=\"dndbeyond:spells/minor-illusion\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/minor-illusion\"><em>minor illusion</em></a> cantrip. If you already know this cantrip, you learn a different mage cantrip of your choice. The cantrip doesn't count against your number of cantrips known.</p>\n<p>When you cast <a class=\"extiw\" title=\"dndbeyond:spells/minor-illusion\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/minor-illusion\"><em>minor illusion</em></a>, you can create both a sound and an image with a single casting of the spell.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 117","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"School of Illusion 2","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_rvadfrusd1s","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Mage Feats#/CF_SEP/Illusion","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"S8QMlXH4KDkI7TZq","name":"Path Spells","type":"feat","img":"UESTRPG/Icons/Classes/Nightblade/Shadow/ON-icon-skill-Shadow-Refreshing_Path.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<h2><span id=\"Path_Spells\" class=\"mw-headline\">Path Spells</span></h2>\n<p>The path of shadow that you follow grants you the ability to cast certain spells. At 3rd, 5th, 7th, and 9th level, you gain access to path spells. <br /><br />Once you gain access to a path spell, you always know it, and it doesn't count against the number of spells you know. If you gain access to a spell that doesn't appear on the <a title=\"BR:Nightblade Spells\" href=\"https://wiki.uestrpg.com/wiki/BR:Nightblade_Spells\">nightblade spell list</a>, the spell is nonetheless a nightblade spell for you.</p>\n<table class=\"uestrpgtable\"><caption>Trickster Spells</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th>Nightblade Level</th>\n<th>Path Spells</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1st</td>\n<td><a class=\"extiw\" title=\"dndbeyond:spells/dissonant-whispers\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/dissonant-whispers\"><em>dissonant whispers</em></a>, <a class=\"extiw\" title=\"dndbeyond:spells/Tashas-hideous-laughter\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/Tashas-hideous-laughter\"><em>Tasha’s hideous laughter</em></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3rd</td>\n<td><a class=\"extiw\" title=\"dndbeyond:spells/detect-thoughts\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/detect-thoughts\"><em>detect life</em></a>, <a class=\"extiw\" title=\"dndbeyond:spells/phantasmal-force\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/phantasmal-force\"><em>phantasmal force</em></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5th</td>\n<td><a class=\"extiw\" title=\"dndbeyond:spells/clairvoyance\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/clairvoyance\"><em>clairvoyance</em></a>, <a class=\"extiw\" title=\"dndbeyond:spells/sending\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/sending\"><em>sending</em></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>7th</td>\n<td><a class=\"extiw\" title=\"dndbeyond:spells/dominate-beast\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/dominate-beast\"><em>dominate beast</em></a>, <a class=\"extiw\" title=\"dndbeyond:spells/black-tentacles\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/black-tentacles\"><em>black tentacles</em></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>9th</td>\n<td><a class=\"extiw\" title=\"dndbeyond:spells/dominate-person\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/dominate-person\"><em>dominate person</em></a>, <a class=\"extiw\" title=\"dndbeyond:spells/telekinesis\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/telekinesis\"><em>telekinesis</em></a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Basic Rules v1.4 pg 75","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Trickster 1","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_4svu3e60w5o","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Nightblade Feats#/CF_SEP/Trickster","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"SErUjvXKC5gsReDp","name":"Fighting Style: Two-Weapon Fighting","type":"feat","img":"icons/skills/melee/weapons-crossed-swords-white-blue.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>When you engage in two-weapon fighting, you can add your ability modifier to the damage of the second attack.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Basic Rules v1.4 pg 39","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"target":{"value":"","width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":"","long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"type":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":"","value":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell","value":""},"requirements":"College of Solitude 3","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dnd5e.classfeatures.mHcSjcHJ8oZu3hkb"},"cf":{"id":"temp_c9gn4tl1e8m","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Bard Feats#/CF_SEP/Solitude","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"SVPpSDtTrb1ayIal","name":"Death Gleaning","type":"feat","img":"modules/uestrpg5e/artwork/ESO/ability/Classes/passive/necromancer_005.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<h3><span id=\"Death_Gleaning\" class=\"mw-headline\">Death Gleaning</span></h3>\n<p>You gain the ability to absorb some of the residual magical energy when a soul is released. Once per turn, when one or more creatures die within 30 feet of you, you regain magicka points equal to the creatures Challenge Rating (CR), to a maximum of one quarter of your necromancer level (rounded up). If more than one creature dies, you only regain magicka points from the creature with the highest CR. If the creature has a CR of less than 1, they do not produce enough magical energy to absorb. You don't gain this benefit for killing constructs or undead.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Enemies of Elsweyr pg 10","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Necromancer 1","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_2vjba2j87na","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Necromancer Feats","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"Sl9H095x6zRDd08q","name":"Minor Conjuration","type":"feat","img":"icons/magic/symbols/runes-carved-stone-purple.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<h2><span id=\"Minor_Conjuration\" class=\"mw-headline\">Minor Conjuration</span></h2>\n<p>Starting at 2nd level when you select this school, you can use your action to conjure up an inanimate object in your hand or on the ground in an unoccupied space that you can see within 10 feet of you. This object can be no larger than 3 feet on a side and weigh no more than 10 pounds, and its form must be that of a non-magical object that you have seen. The object is visibly magical, radiating dim light out to 5 feet.</p>\n<p>The object disappears after 1 hour, when you use this feature again, or if it takes any damage.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB pg. 117","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"School of Conjuration 2","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_5dhrt0nb34x","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Mage Feats#/CF_SEP/Conjuration","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"SzAxNsydw802iSKj","name":"Grisly Totems","type":"feat","img":"modules/uestrpg5e/artwork/ESO/ability/Classes/necromancer/010.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<h2><span id=\"Grisly_Totems\" class=\"mw-headline\">Grisly Totems</span></h2>\n<p>At 2nd level, you are able to use the corpses of the fallen to create grisly magical totems made of bone that can bolster your allies or harm your foes. As a bonus action on your turn, you can use a corpse of a small or larger creature that you can see and transform it into a totem of your choice. The totem is created in a location that you can see within 30 feet of you. The corpse that is used to create the totem is destroyed and can't be used again. If a totem requires a creature to make a saving throw, the DC is determined by your Spell Save DC. <br /><br /><em><strong>Agony Totem.</strong></em> Whenever a creature moves into a space within a 30-foot radius of the totem for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, it takes 1d6 necrotic damage. <br /><br /><em><strong>Bone Totem.</strong></em> You and your allies gain a +1 bonus to AC and saving throws while within a 30-foot radius of the totem. <br /><br /><em><strong>Fear Totem.</strong></em> One creature of your choice within a 30-foot radius of the totem must succeed on a Willpower saving throw or become frightened of you or an ally of your choice. You can use a bonus action on a subsequent turn of yours to attempt to frighten another creature, ending the effect on a creature already frightened by the totem. A creature frightened by the totem can make a Willpower saving throw at the end of each of their turns, ending the effect on a success. <br /><br /><em><strong>Grasping Totem.</strong></em> Whenever a creature moves into a space within a 30-foot radius of the totem for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, it must succeed on an Agility saving throw or become restrained. The restrained creature can make this saving throw again on the start of each of its turns. <br /><br />The totem has 20 hit points and an AC of 12 and remains for 1 hour or until its hit points are reduced to 0 or a new totem is created.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"EoE pg. 17","activation":{"type":"bonus","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":30,"width":null,"units":"","type":"sphere"},"range":{"value":30,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":""},"consume":{"type":"attribute","target":"","amount":1},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Undying Warrior 2","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7p78eooyEyF8LXNq":3},"flags":{"midi-qol":{"effectActivation":false},"cf":{"id":"temp_2rtozgv034h","path":"Class Features#/CF_SEP/Necromancer Feats#/CF_SEP/Undying Warrior","color":"#000000"}}}
